<subSubSection id="A1066760D4F5AB4CCE29D0E3065C9761" type="key">
<paragraph id="10A2D9E43E31F266D0EFC0CB0B055A60" pageNumber="41">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="5B5E7E27BF3F1ED5A53BD3F4A5B2A135" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Plagioscion</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD6FF5081FB1DF3CF29E8CE96399F1BB" pageNumber="41">1. Distance from anus to origin of anal fin 1.9-3.5 in HL (mean 2.7) (Fig. 1A) .............. 2</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44E1F68FA33D74618D9BFECB39AFFD6B" pageNumber="41">
- Distance from anus to origin of anal fin 3.6-5.6 in HL (mean 4.4 [10% of the individuals recognized as 
<taxonomicName id="6412A56A2046065D29C5EE3A52F0E91D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamosissimus">Plagioscion squamosissimus</taxonomicName>
can show this value ranging from 3.1 to 3.5]) (Fig. 1B) .......................................................................................................... 4
</paragraph>
